text.tspan: Computation used to train notable AI systems, by affiliation of researchers
Computation is measured in total petaFLOP, which is 10¹⁵ floating-point operations.
Note: A research collective is a group of AI researchers not organized under an academic or industry affiliation. Computation is estimated based
on published results in the AI literature and comes with some uncertainty. The authors expect most of these estimates to be correct within a factor
of 2, and a factor of 5 for recent models for which relevant numbers were not disclosed, such as GPT-4.
